@Code
    PageData("Title") = "Design Style: Coastal"
    PageData("art_sub_title") = ""
    Layout = "~/_DTLayout.vbhtml"
    PageData("description") = "The sea allures us with its untamed beauty. From cresting waves to sandy shorelines, the sea coast is a ceaseless inspiration."
End Code

	
<div class="spacer"></div>
<p class="opening">@PageData("description")</p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Providing a plethora of palettes, it is no surprise that the sea and its coastlines have found their way into our homes. It is the simple nature of coastal design that has been inspiring interiors around the world for centuries. </p>

<p>No matter where your home is located, there are certain aesthetics that are found in all coastal designs. These interiors are simplistic, honoring the sea and its sandy environment. Drawing from this, the color palette remains pure and simple. Varying whites and blues provide a fresh foundation for the home's design. Accenting with soft, sandy hues or strong, nautical tones allows the coastal vibe to wash freely throughout the home. On the other end of the spectrum, these interiors also embrace the warmth of coral. A cheerful mix of varying undertones, coral and its color companions have a unique glow that immediately adds life to any space. Similarly, splashy shades that are bright and fun can also be found within these designs. However, they must be kept in check or the interiors may begin to feel more carefree Caribbean than calming coastal. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center"><a href="http://www.houseofturquoise.com/2015/02/cove-interiors.html" target="_blank">
		<img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Coastal-LR2.jpg"></a></div>
<div class="spacer"></div>
		
<p>This applies not only to wall colors and decor but also to the textiles found within the home. Unassuming and simplistic, these fabrics must flow seamlessly into the homes design. Linen, cotton, and muslin are among the favorites, with calico and even raw silk making appearances. The natural hand and appearance of these is what makes them a favorite in coastal interiors. Outside of the simple solids, prints are a great way to add a little depth and a lot of character. But, these must be used sparingly so as not to overthrow the essence of the room's design. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

