<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Just like the beach breezes that flow, coastal interiors have an easy, wandering design. Clear sight-lines and minimal furnishings allow for the freeness these designs desire. Rather than focusing on the center of a space, coastal interiors instead focus on their periphery. This keeps those coastal views the center of the design. Thus, plentiful windows are key to these interiors. Not only do they unveil the view beyond, they allow coastal interiors' best accessory to stream in- natural light. The sun is as important to coastal interiors as it is to beach-goers. Its brilliance brings an unmatchable beauty into the home. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center" class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<a href="http://willeydesign.com/projects/sag-harbor" target="_blank">
		<img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Coastal-LR6.jpg"></a>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
