		<img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Coastal-LR8.jpg"></a>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Beach homes exude a relaxed beauty that withstands its oft harsh environment. Durable, worry-free furnishings are essential to a coastal home's interior. With sand, shells, and salty water frequently finding its way into the home, everyday fixtures like couches and chairs must resist the wear and tear of daily beach life. With today's advancements in textile technology, outdoor upholstery is finding its way inside coastal interiors as well as remaining outside it. Furnishings are frequently made from materials that are known to endure, such as wicker and weathered wood. Driftwood is immensely popular, along with ash, blond maple, and even bamboo as choices for furnishings and floorings. These options give coastal interiors the natural, earthy feel they're known for. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center" class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<a href="http://village-architects.com/beach-cottage/" target="_blank">
		<img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Coastal-LR4.jpg"></a>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<a href="http://www.woodmeister.com/living-rooms" target="_blank">
		<img class="img-responsive" alt="" src="~/designthreads/images/DesignStyle-Coastal-LR7.jpg"></a>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Just as the shorelines are awash with textural elements, so too are coastal interiors. From driftwood and sea shells, to jute and sisal, the senses come alive within these designs. The earthy, organic fibers add life and substance without overwhelming the space. However, with so many choices it is easy to drench the home in coastal accoutrements. It is crucial to keep these elements to a minimum so as to not compromise the serene effect of the design. </p>
<div class="spacer"></div>

<div align="center" class="row">
